\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{obj_create}

\end_inset 

Creating Objects
\layout Standard

Loading a dataset is the first step to visualization.
 Creating an 
\emph on 
object
\emph default 
 from the dataset is the second.
 Objects are an interpretation of the data stored within the dataset and
 they are displayed in the graphics window.
\layout Standard

Some datasets support different types of objects, varying in their interpretatio
n of the data.
 For example, a macromolecular structure can be represented as atoms connected
 with bonds or as a backbone trace, resulting in two different object types
 for the structure dataset (named, surprisingly, 
\family typewriter 
connect
\family default 
 and 
\family typewriter 
trace
\family default 
).
\layout Standard

Just as there is no limitation on the amount of datasets, there is no limitation
 on the number of object.
 An object always belongs to the dataset it was created from.
\layout Standard

The following command is used to create an object from a dataset:
\layout Code

.DS new [-name N] [-type T] [-set SET] [-sel SEL]
\layout Standard

The target dataset precedes 
\family typewriter 
new
\family default 
, since this is a dataset command.
 There are four optional parameters:
\layout Description


\family typewriter 
-name\SpecialChar ~
N 
\family default 
Denotes the name given to the object.
 If omitted, the dataset name is used.
\layout Description


\family typewriter 
-type\SpecialChar ~
T 
\family default 
Determines an object type, if the dataset supports several.
 The default one will be used if omitted.
\layout Description


\family typewriter 
-set\SpecialChar ~
SET 
\family default 
Allows object properties (see 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \vref{obj_create}

\end_inset 

) to be set during creation.
\layout Description


\family typewriter 
-sel\SpecialChar ~
SEL 
\family default 
Specifies a selection to include only a subset of the data.
\layout Standard

In Chapter 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \vref{datasets}

\end_inset 

, the 
\family typewriter 
new
\family default 
 command will be explained in detail for each dataset.
\layout Standard

During object creation, properties are copied or linked
